{
  "texts": [
    "Depending on the application, Root Mean Square Error (RMSE) or confusion matrices are typically used as measures of model performance.",
    "Hence, if the model fails to interpret data with a pre-defined accuracy, the model is required to be re-developed.",
    "For more detail explanations about the workflow of ML algorithms, some previous works can be referred as (Bonaccorso, 2018; Janiesch et al., 2021; Mohammed et al., 2016).",
    "Figure 8 depicts the complete process of ML algorithms through a block diagram.",
    "ML algorithms can be classified into supervised and unsupervised learning based on their learning approaches, primarily though some works add semi-supervised learning and reinforcement learning (Kumar et al., 2019)."
  ]
}